SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: RESTORATION CENTER PROVIDES FOOD CLOTHING AND TOILETRIES TO LOW-INCOME AND HOMELESS FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS. EACH FAMILY OR INDIVIDUAL COMPLETES A BASIC APPLICATION INCLUDING INFORMATION ABOUT INCOME AND ANY OTHER ASSISTANCE RECEIVED. RESORATION CENTER ALSO HOLDS A MONTHLY MOBILE FOOD PANTRY TO DISBURSE FOOD DONATED BY THE TARRANT AREA FOOD BANK. TO RECEIVE FOOD FROM THE MOBILE PANTRY INDIVIDUALS AND FAMILIES MUST COMPLETE AN APPLICATION PROVIDED BY THE FOOD BANK INCLUDING INFORMATION ABOUT OTHER ASSISTANCE RECEIVED INCOME AND EMERGENCY SITUATIONS. IN ADDITION TO FOOD DISTRIBUTION RESTORATION CENTER PROVIDES FINANCIAL ASSISTACE FOR HOUSING UTILTIES AND OTHER MISC. BASIC NEEDS. TO RECEIVE FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS MUST COMPLETE AN APPLICATION AND INTERVIEW AND THE HOUSING LANDLORD MUST ALSO BE INTERVIEWED TO DETERMINE ELIGIBILITY. HOUSING ASSISTANCE IS PAID DIRECTLY TO THE LANDLORD AND UTILITY ASSISTANCE IS PAID DIRECTLY TO THE UTILITY COMPANY.
